<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-06-07T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-06-07T15:00:00-05:00" n="394" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d394">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.124a/71: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Carter</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-06-07T16:00:00-04:00">June 7, 1930—4
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>55. Reference your No. 68, May 25, noon, last paragraph. Advisory
                            Committee reports that it is sending $2,000 to Campbell today for
                            sanitary relief.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>